Welcome to the Kids' Picture Show! We use simple, clear language to teach basic concepts in language and math to toddlers, preschoolers, kindergartners and elementary school-age students. Our videos reach a broad international audience and promote children's reading readiness and literacy. Kids can learn animals, vehicles, verbs, food groups, planets, shapes, colors, numbers, the alphabet, communications skills and more.

We have a board book series published by Penguin Workshop based on our popular vehicles and animals videos. The child literacy experts from Dolly Parton's Imagination Library even selected our books as USA Blue Ribbon Selections for 2020 and 2021!

Our videos are great for all kids including reluctant learners, visual learners, ESL students and children with developmental disabilities such as autism. The clear and simple animated visuals and audio cues are designed to encourage children to read and vocalize. Parents and educators can read along, too. Check us out!

description:
I have been around bikes and cars since before i was able to walk.  I grew up helping my dad do small engine repair in his shop and i ended up with a motorcycle before i had a car!  I started out on a 79 sportster in high school and quickly realized it wasn't fast enough so i bought my dads 03 buell xb9s and rode that until the transmission gave up!  So i moved on to a 08 buell 1125r which i had for a year before deciding to trade it plus some cash for my dads 67 nova.  I then went a year without a bike and couldn't take it anymore so i ended up picking up the 07 zx14 which has been a awesome bike that has been a part of many great videos now!!  

I just enjoy getting out with the guys and having a good time with the bikes and some days we spend more time hanging out bs'n than we do riding, but occasionally we get some good videos!

description:
Pink Floyd, one of the most successful and influential groups ever, formed in the 1960s when Roger Waters, Nick Mason and Richard Wright were studying at college in London. They added Roger ‘Syd’ Barrett, a Cambridge friend, who named the band after bluesmen Pink Anderson and Floyd Council.
 
Debut album The Piper At The Gates Of Dawn is still considered one of the greatest psychedelic albums, but in 1968 Syd Barrett’s erratic behaviour prompted his replacement by David Gilmour, another friend. Pink Floyd developed the members’ compositional and improvisational talents, and built a large audience via many live tours, releasing a succession of hit albums, including The Dark Side Of The Moon, Wish You Were Here, and The Wall.
 
Roger Waters left in 1985, but the band enjoyed continuing success with the studio albums A Momentary Lapse Of Reason and The Division Bell, accompanied by world tours. The final Pink Floyd release was 2014’s The Endless River, another worldwide #1 album.

description:
I have decided to make this channel on youtube in order to keep myself motivated in keeping up with working out as im getting older. I was born in 1981 and now I could feel that my body is not how it used to be in the my 20s. I get injured easier now and my lower back is having problems and it feels like my back is injured more often than not. I tried going to the gym here and there, but seems like each time i try, i re-injure myself again, so i had to take some time off. 

I have decided to take it easy, take my time, Since its been a long while since i been to the gym. I have lost a lot of my gains that i had. Being older, you get smarter, there is no need to impress the world, but only to take it easy and enjoy doing it. In high school and collegel years you only have a limited amount of time to impress your friends and girls, now that im married and have kids and have a job, im the only one left to impress, so i have all my life to impress myself :)

description:
This is my gaming video account, my normal account is also ddraig au (beats me)

(old, see update below) At the moment this is almost entirely Planetside 2 footage - as that's about the only game I play lately.  This footage is recorded originally @ 60fps / 1080p using shadowplay, and then compressed into x264 / 30fps and uploaded here. No voice comms is recorded, only what comes out of the speakers.   Since dropping the shadowplay buffer from 20 minutes to 10 minutes I seem to not have stuttering issues - interesting.

Update: 4k footage, 20 minute buffer again, I'll record voice comms, because after 10 years of not recording voices, I think that was a bad idea.  *shrug*. I'm also playing games other than Planetside 2, lately - although that is still my favourite game

description:
Hi, I'm the Internet traveler, Luigifan.  You may recognize me from some other websites...  I'm known as Luigifan on Wikipedia, Luigifan18 here, on GameFAQs and on DeviantART, Luigifan1 on Fanfiction.net, Matthew or Luigifan on Songfacts.com, and Luigifan on Cracked.com.

For my first year with this account, I didn't post any videos of my own, instead contenting myself with going around and commenting on others.  My comments are generally favorable, so don't worry about being bashed.  :p  I first broke into bona-fide video production upon recieving a digital camera for my 18th birthday (specifically an Olympus waterproof camera,) which was capable of taking both pictures and videos.  Its video quality is somewhat poor, especially in terms of the sound... but what the hey, it's better than nothing.  I use the same camera for most of my images on DeviantART.  I got a JVC HDD digital camcorder for that year's Christmas, but that saves videos as MOD files, and getting them onto YouTube requires me to get them into an acceptable format with the AVS Video Converter - which can be a tedious process (especially now that my AVS Video Converter is broken, due to faulty video drivers or something like that.)

I've also discovered how to use Windows Movie Maker, and it's now the primary means I use to produce my videos.  I didn't have many audio files at first, but built up my collection by scrounging around the CDs at my house and my brother's iTunes collection (as well as the occasional direct rip from YouTube via SaveVids.com, AVS Video Converter, and AVS Audio Editor.)  Now I have more than I really know what to do with!!!  I also recently purchased the Pixelan Effects Pack to replace the Pan and Zoom effects I lost when my old laptop got too virus-riddled to function, and I had to get a replacement.  I decided to get everything else as part of the bargain (I was initially going to buy just five packs, when I noticed that I could buy all of them for less... funny how that worked, huh?)  As for my images and video clips, I get most of those from DeviantART, YouTube (via SaveVids.com,) and my trusty digital camera.

description:
Before television, people came to movie theatres to watch the news. British Pathé was at the forefront of cinematic journalism, blending information with entertainment to popular effect. Over the course of a century, it documented everything from major armed conflicts and seismic political crises to the curious hobbies and eccentric lives of ordinary people.

Now considered to be the finest newsreel archive in the world, British Pathé is a treasure trove of 85,000 films unrivalled in their historical and cultural significance.

British Pathé also represents the Reuters historical collection, which includes more than 136,000 items from the news agencies Gaumont Graphic (1910-1932), Empire News Bulletin (1926-1930), British Paramount (1931-1957), and Gaumont British (1934-1959), as well as Visnews content from 1957 to the end of 1984. description:
PTZPros.com was formed in February 2011 by partners, Chad Stone, Justin Harris, and Steven Pickett. Our goal was to procure affordable, yet high quality professional surveillance equipment that rivaled the performance of that which is used in mega-footprint applications such as casinos and retail centers.

Having spent over 30 plus years as installation professionals, surveillance advisors and more, we set out to find the most affordable, high-quality auto-tracking PTZ cameras that we were confident we could stand behind. The products on our website provide the best of the best sought after features available. Features such as auto-tracking, infrared illumination, and zone and pattern patrolling are standards in the cameras we sell.

Hallo, en welkom op mijn YouTube kanaal. Ik ben Koplopermau en mijn passie is treinen, reizen, openbaar vervoer en techniek. Op mijn YouTube kanaal upload ik beelden van treinen, maar rij ik ook regelmatig in het spel 'Train Simulator'.

Voor het maken van de beelden reis ik regelmatig door heel Nederland en daarbuiten om treinen en openbaar vervoer te filmen. Deze beelden monteer ik aan elkaar met Sony Vegas Pro en zet ik vervolgens op YouTube, zowel oud als nieuw. Er gaat dus veel werk in zitten, aangezien mijn video's ook nog eens op 4k kwaliteit worden opgenomen.

Mijn planning bestaat uit elke woensdag een treinen compilatie. Deze komt live om 12:00. Op zondag upload ik een Train Simulator video, ook om 12:00. De rest van de week upload ik highlights, bijzondere treinen en video's van de compilatie van de week.

Ben jij ook een treinenfan, abonneer je dan snel. Veel kijkplezier!

description:
Rae Sremmurd is a Tupelo, MS born hip hop duo comprised of brothers Swae Lee and Slim Jxmmi. 

The pair signed to EarDrummers Entertainment on January 1, 2014. They released their debut album, SremmLife, on January 6, 2015 which debuted at number 5 on the US Billboard 200.  Its lead single, "No Flex Zone,” released in 2014, gained considerable attention after it was officially remixed featuring rappers Nicki Minaj and Pusha T. The single peaked at number 36 on the US Billboard Hot 100. Their second single, "No Type" climbed to number 16 on the Billboard Hot 100. Both singles were certified platinum by the Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA).

On August 12 2016, Rae Sremmurd released their second studio album, SremmLife 2, on Ear Drummer Records/ Interscope Records. The album includes the duo’s first Billboard number-one song "Black Beatles", which topped the chart in the issue dated November 26, 2016 and held the number one spot for seven consecutive weeks.

description:
Seit 1981 setzen wir bei Weber mit Innovationskraft, Qualität und Kundennähe neue Maßstäbe. Begonnen hat damals alles in der Herstellung von Entschwartungs- und Entvliesmaschinen (sog. Skinner), die auch noch heute fester Bestandteil unseres Produktportfolios sind. Mittlerweile hat sich Weber als einer der führenden Systemanbieter für Aufschnittanwendungen etabliert. Wir sind stolz darauf, ein starker Partner der lebensmittelverarbeitenden Industrie zu sein.

Vom gewichtsgenauen Schneiden bis zum präzisen Einlegen und Verpacken von Wurst, Fleisch, Käse und veganen Ersatzprodukten: wir entwickeln und produzieren komplette Schneide- und Verpackungslinien für die Verarbeitung von Lebensmitteln. Unser Portfolio ist vielfältig, und bietet für alle Anforderungen und Anwendungsbereiche die perfekte Lösung. Das bedeutet auch, unsere Kunden vor Ort mit eigenen Mitarbeitern zu unterstützen.

The 419th Fighter Wing is made up of nearly 1,300 personnel. These “Citizen Airmen” serve part time in the military, but are full-time members of the local community. Most live, work, and raise families in Northern Utah. 419th FW members regularly volunteer to deploy in support of contingency operations and humanitarian efforts around the world. The wing offers a diverse range of combat capability to include F-35 operations and maintenance, as well as full-spectrum mission support such as civil engineering, security forces, medical, aerial port, firefighting, supply, and transportation. The 419th FW was the first Air Force Reserve unit to fly the F-35A Lightning II alongside the active-duty 388th FW at Hill Air Force Base, Utah.

Learn more about the Fighter Wing and its mission at: https://www.419fw.afrc.af.mil/

description:
MIT Corporate Relations aids and directs companies interested in multidisciplinary involvement with the Institute. It offers industry access to MIT through two integrated programs, the MIT Industrial Liaison Program (ILP) and MIT Startup Exchange. 

The Industrial Liaison Program is instrumental in providing connections to MIT faculty, departments, labs, and centers. It serves companies across the globe and is organized both geographically and by industry. MIT Startup Exchange actively promotes collaboration and partnerships between MIT-connected startups and industry. Qualified startups are those founded and/or led by MIT faculty, staff, or alumni, or are based on MIT-licensed technology. Industry participants are principally members of MIT’s Industrial Liaison Program (ILP).

description: Stillstand ist nicht sein Ding. BOSSE wirbelt wieder! Auf seinem mittlerweile siebten Studioalbum mit dem vortrefflich gewählten Titel „Alles ist jetzt“, das am 12. Oktober 2018 erschienen und gleich auf #1 der Album Charts eingestiegen ist!. Dies ist nach dem "Engtanz“ Album bereits die zweite Nummer 1 Platzierung in Folge für Bosse. Der Vorgänger „Kraniche“ ist mit GOLD für über 100.000 verkaufte Alben dekoriert. Er hat den ,,Bundesvision Song Contest’’ gewonnen, ist mit dem ,,Deutschen Musikautorenpreis’’ ausgezeichnet worden und hat den Hamburger Musikpreis ,,Hans’’ gleich dreifach eingeheimst. Zu einem der etabliertesten und anerkanntesten Künstler im Live-Business zu gehören: wohl die schönste Auszeichnung für Kontinuität und das größte Geschenk, was einem das eigene Publikum machen kann. Vor über 13.000 Fans beim eigenen Open-Air-Konzert auf der Hamburger Trabrennbahn und über 100.000 BesucherInnen auf der Tour zum letzten Album zu spielen. Clubkonzerte innerhalb von zwei Minuten auszuverkaufen: BOSSE ist ein Magnet. Nicht nur musikalisch. Sein Antrieb: Jeder Schritt nach vorne setzt Energie frei. Jedes durchschwitzte Konzert Liebe. Jedes neue Album Dankbarkeit.

description:
Official YouTube Channel of Nancy Sinatra. 

Equal parts strong, sultry, and savvy, Nancy Sinatra has long been ahead of her time – both in her choices as an artist and as a business-woman. Unapologetically, she established her own path early-on and paved the way for decades of female artists to come – all while firmly maintaining control over her career, her image, and her music. Sinatra’s legacy continues to grow, as new generations discovered her music. Over the years, she has been cited as an influence by countless artists, including Madonna, Kacey Musgraves, Sonic Youth, Morrissey, Calexico, U2, and Lana Del Rey. Most recently, her contributions to the industry were further recognized by her peers, when “Boots” was inducted into the GRAMMY® Hall of Fame. The honor, bestowed in January of 2020, recognizes “musical recordings of lasting qualitative or historical significance.” Today, Sinatra continues to be a passionate voice for a variety of progressive causes – most notably her support of veterans. A self-proclaimed feminist, Sinatra’s advocacy also extends to her fellow female artists.

description:
MIKROTRON - a brand of SVS-Vistek GmbH

The MIKROTRON brand is internationally known in the machine vision market for small, particularly robust High-Speed cameras that are used in industrial and scientific applications as well as in sports, advertising and nature filming.

SVS-Vistek GmbH has exceptional know-how in industrial image processing as an innovative manufacturer of high-quality industrial CCD and CMOS cameras for more than 35 years. 
We develop and produce a wide range of standard cameras as well as cameras with the highest resolutions and highest speeds, above-average image quality and all relevant interfaces in our own clean rooms at our headquarters in Gilching near Munich: Quality Made in Germany! 
With subsidiaries in the USA and Japan as well as a large partner network, we can advise, support and serve customers of many markets worldwide.

We want to show that everyone in the world is the best at something and we’re here to measure it! 

If you’ve got the stretchiest skin, know the world’s smallest dog or want to create the largest human dominoes chain, we want to hear about it. 

Here on the Guinness World Records YouTube channel we want to showcase incredible talent. If you're looking for videos featuring the world's tallest, shortest, fastest, longest, oldest and most incredible things on the planet, you're in the right place.

We know you're all fab, but here are some short house rules:

• Please be respectful of each other and of our record holders.
• We will always welcome new applications - if you think you can break a record, please do apply. 
• Spam posts will result in an instant ban.
• If you have a question about an application or a customer services issue you'd like to raise with the team, please head to www.guinnessworldrecords.com/contact to send a message.

description:
GIBBS AMPHIBIANS ARE WORLD LEADERS IN THE DEVELOPMENT AND LICENSING OF HIGH SPEED AMPHIBIOUS TECHNOLOGIES
Gibbs Amphibians is the first company in history to successfully create fully homologated vehicles that can exceed 30 mph on water as well as achieve typical speeds on land, transitioning between land and water in under 5 seconds, at the push of a button. This unique combination of innovations from several engineering disciplines and user friendly technology has given Gibbs the lead as the world authority on High Speed Amphibians.
Gibbs has been developing High Speed Amphibian (HSA) technology since 1994, creating the record breaking and award winning Aquada in 2003, the Humdinga in 2005, the Phibian in 2012 and the Quadski in 2013, with Quadski XL being added to the product range in 2014. Following on from this, three further platforms have been added; Biski, Triski, and the Terraquad. Details of all HSA variants listed above are on our website.

description:
Imaging beyond the standard!

XIMEA, with its 25 years of experience in the industry, develops high-end industrial and scientific cameras, getting the best out of the latest sensors in the most compact design.

Today, XIMEA provides standard and OEM cameras for numerous applications, e.g. in the fields of medicine, astronomy, entertainment, security or agriculture. The portfolio spans from very compact board level cameras over hyperspectral imaging, high-resolution and high-speed cameras to multi-camera platforms which supports over a hundred sensors in a single setup. All cameras and setups are manufactured with modern interfaces like USB3 and PCI Express.

By combining the best technologies with the most compact designs, XIMEA’s cameras constantly incorporate state-of-the-art products that lift the bar for the competitors on the market. 

Innovation creates the technology for tomorrow by pushing the envelope today. 
That is our passion. That is us. XIMEA.

Learn more at www.ximea.com

description:
This is the now-retired channel of travel author Josh Summers, documenting his decade of life in China's western region of Xinjiang.

For most people, Xinjiang is known as the place of concentration camps, oppression and cultural genocide. While this is true, what gets lost in the news is the incredible beauty of the Uyghur culture and the breathtaking scenery of the region.

Josh's videos remain here as a time capsule of a history and culture that is slowly being erased. Most of what you'll see no longer exists today.

If you'd like to connect with Josh - even though he is no longer in Xinjiang - you can do so here:
  **Instagram** - https://www.instagram.com/joshssummers
  **LinkedIn** - https://www.linkedin.com/in/joshssummers

For all inquiries related to licensing of footage, please use the email address listed under "business inquiries". Thank you.

description:
The Micro/Nano Technology Center (MNTC) is a core facility at the the University of Louisville that is comprised of two laboratories.  The first is a class 100/1000 $30 million 10,000 ft2 cleanroom facility.  The second facility is the Huson Imaging & Characterization Laboratory.  The Center’s expertise resides in micro and nanotechnology, sensors, transducers, microelectromechanical systems (MEMS), advanced materials, biomedical devices, space, and governmental applications that supports a wide range of research initiated by faculty, academic institutions, start-ups, medium and large businesses around the country. 

The MNTC is part of the KY Multiscale Node which is a member of the National Nanotechnology Coordinated Infrastructure network.

Comments on videos are typically disabled as we do not have resources for proper moderation. If you actually want to reach the speakers we recommend to reach out via the contact details on their lecture slides.
